The paper discusses self-adaptive systems, which are a subfield of software engineering (cs.SE) that deals with systems that can change their behaviour in response to changes in their environment. The paper also discusses the need to preserve functional requirements while accommodating variations in non-functional requirements (NFRs), which is a common concern in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper proposes a formal method for analysing conformance to NFRs, which involves partial satisfaction of requirements, which is a topic in cryptography (cs.CR) and programming languages (cs.PL).
